<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-14-0826 </DOCNO><TEXT>This article describes a computer-aided system using automatic laser scanningtechniques to restore the quality of ancient substation drawings. Existingdrawings are scanned, cleaned, amended and stored on a computer. Oncethe drawings have been processed they remain in pristine condition andcan be recalled for further amendment using computer-aided techniqueswithout loss of quality. The use of automatic scanning techniques willalso facilitate data input to computerised mains records and graphicalinformation systems, and this application is briefly considered.</TEXT></DOC>